The Iranian parliament passed a law on Wednesday  authorising the government to raise its share in the International Finance  Corporation (IFC), a subsidiary of the World Bank.
The law would allow the government to raise the value of its assets from  816,000 dollars to 1.4 million dollars, according to parliamentary sources.
Iran last raised its share in the IFC in August 1991 from 372,000 dollars  to 816,000 dollars.
The World Bank granted three loans to Iran in 1993.
